    "Crucially, the civil rights movement is generally seen as the period during which racism shifted from overt to covert 68, 69, and this is mirrored by our results: all the language models overtly agree the most with human stereotypes from after the civil rights movement, but covertly agree the most with human stereotypes from before the civil rights movement.",
    "Our findings beg the question of how dialect prejudice got into the language models.",
    "Language models are pretrained on web-scraped corpora such as WebText 46, C4 (ref.",
